1	-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2	-- Title      : RSSI Protocol: https://confluence.slac.stanford.edu/x/1IyfD
3	-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4	-- Company    : SLAC National Accelerator Laboratory
5	-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6	-- Description: The module is based upon RUDP (Cisco implementation) RFC-908, RFC-1151, draft-ietf-sigtran-reliable-udp-00.
7	--              The specifications in the drafts are modified by internal simplifications and improvements.
8	--
9	--              Interfaces to transport and application side through AxiStream ports
10	--              The AxiStream IO port widths can be adjusted (AxiStream FIFOs added to IO)
11	--              Optional AxiLite Register interface. More info on registers is in RssiAxiLiteRegItf.vhd
12	--              The module can act as Server or Client:
13	--                 - Server: - Passively listens for connection request from client,
14	--                           - Monitors connection activity NULL segment timeouts
15	--                 - Client: - Actively requests connection
16	--                           - Sends NULL packages if there is no incoming data
17	--  Status register:
18	--    statusReg_o(0) : Connection Active
19	--    statusReg_o(1) : Maximum retransmissions exceeded r.retransMax and
20	--    statusReg_o(2) : Null timeout reached (server) r.nullTout;
21	--    statusReg_o(3) : Error in acknowledgment mechanism
22	--    statusReg_o(4) : SSI Frame length too long
23	--    statusReg_o(5) : Connection to peer timed out
24	--    statusReg_o(6) : Client rejected the connection (parameters out of range)
25	--                     Server proposed new parameters (parameters out of range)
26	-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
27	-- This file is part of 'SLAC Firmware Standard Library'.
28	-- It is subject to the license terms in the LICENSE.txt file found in the
29	-- top-level directory of this distribution and at:
30	--    https://confluence.slac.stanford.edu/display/ppareg/LICENSE.html.
31	-- No part of 'SLAC Firmware Standard Library', including this file,
32	-- may be copied, modified, propagated, or distributed except according to
33	-- the terms contained in the LICENSE.txt file.
34	-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
35	
36	library ieee;
37	use ieee.std_logic_1164.all;
38	use ieee.std_logic_unsigned.all;
39	use ieee.std_logic_arith.all;
40	use ieee.math_real.all;
41	
42	
43	library surf;
