1	-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2	-- Title      : RSSI Protocol: https://confluence.slac.stanford.edu/x/1IyfD
3	-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4	-- Company    : SLAC National Accelerator Laboratory
5	-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6	-- Description: Transmitter FSM
7	--              Transmitter has the following functionality:
8	--              Handle buffer addresses and buffer window (firstUnackAddr,nextSentAddr,lastSentAddr, bufferFull, bufferEmpty)
9	--              Application side FSM. Receive SSI frame and store into TX data buffer.
10	--                   - IDLE Waits until buffer window is free (not bufferFull),
11	--                   - Waits for Application side SOF,
12	--                   - Save the segment to Rx buffer at nextSentAddr. Disable sending of NULL segments with appBusy flag,
13	--                   - When EOF received save segment length and keep flags. Check length error,
14	--                   - Request data send at Transport side FSM and increment nextSentAddr
15	--                   - Wait until the data is processed and data segment sent by Transport side FSM
16	--                   - Release appBusy flag and go back to INIT.
17	--              Acknowledgment FSM.
18	--                   - IDLE Waits for ack_i (ack request) and ackN_i(ack number)(from RxFSM),
19	--                   - Increments firstUnackAddr until the ackN_i is found in Window buffer,
20	--                   - If it does not find the SEQ number it reports Ack Error,
21	--                   - Goes back to IDLE.
22	--              Transport side FSM. Send and resend various segments to Transport side.
23	--                   - INIT Initializes seqN to initSeqN. Waits until new connection requested. ConnFSM going out of Closed state.
24	--                   - DISS_CONN allows sending SYN, ACK, or RST segments. Goes to CONN when connection becomes active.
25	--                   - CONN allows sending DATA, NULL, ACK, or RST segments.
26	--                     In Resend procedure the FSM resends all the unacknowledged (DATA, NULL, RST) segments in the buffer window.
27	--
28	--              Note:Sequence number is incremented with sending SYN, DATA, NULL, and RST segments.
29	--              Note:Only the following segments are saved into Tx buffer DATA, NULL, and RST.
30	-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
