1	-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2	-- Title      : RSSI Protocol: https://confluence.slac.stanford.edu/x/1IyfD
3	-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4	-- Company    : SLAC National Accelerator Laboratory
5	-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6	-- Description:  Register decoding for RSSI core
7	--               0x00 (RW)- Control register [4:0]:
8	--                   bit 0: Open connection request (Default '0')
9	--                   bit 1: Close connection request (Default '0')
10	--                   bit 2: Mode (Default '0'):
11	--                            - '0': Use internal parameters from generics
12	--                            - '1': Use parameters from Axil
13	--                   bit 3: Header checksum enable (Default '1')
14	--                   bit 4: Inject fault to the next packet header checksum (Default '0')
15	--                            Acts on rising edge - injects exactly one fault in next segment (ACK, NULL, or DATA)
16	--               0x01 (RW)- Initial sequence number [7:0] (Default x"80")
17	--               0x02 (RW)- Version register [3:0](Default x"1")
18	--               0x03 (RW)- Maximum out standing segments [7:0](Default "008"):
19	--                            Defines the max number of segments in the RSSI receiver buffer
20	--               0x04 (RW)- Maximum segment size [15:0](Default x"0400")
21	--                            Defines the size of segment buffer! Number of bytes!
22	--               0x05 (RW)- Retransmission timeout [15:0](Default 50)
23	--                            Unit depends on TIMEOUT_UNIT_G
24	--               0x06 (RW)- Cumulative acknowledgment timeout [15:0](Default 50)
25	--                            Unit depends on TIMEOUT_UNIT_G
26	--               0x07 (RW)- Null segment timeout [15:0](Default 50)
27	--                            Unit depends on TIMEOUT_UNIT_G
28	--                            Server: Close connection if Null segment missed!
29	--                            Client: Transmit Null segment when nullSegTout/2 reached!
30	--               0x08 (RW)- Maximum number of retransmissions [7:0](Default x"02")
31	--                            How many times segments are retransmitted before the connection gets broken.
32	--               0x09 (RW)- Maximum cumulative acknowledgments [7:0](Default x"03")
33	--                            When more than maxCumAck are received and not acknowledged the
34	--                            ACK packet will be sent to acknowledge the received packets. Even though the
35	--                            cumulative acknowledgment timeout has not been reached yet!
36	--               0x0A (RW)- Max out of sequence segments (EACK) [7:0](Default x"03")
37	--                            Currently not used TBD
38	--               0x0B (RW)- Connection ID [31:0](Default x"12345678")
39	--                            Every connection should have unique connection ID.
40	--               Statuses
41	--               0x10 (R)- Status register [5:0]:
42	--                   bit(0) : Connection Active
43	--                   bit(1) : Maximum retransmissions exceeded retransMax
44	--                   bit(2) : Null timeout reached (server) r.nullTout
45	--                   bit(3) : Error in acknowledgment mechanism
46	--                   bit(4) : SSI Frame length too long
47	--                   bit(5) : Connection to peer timed out
48	--                   bit(6) : Parameters from peer rejected (Client) or new proposed(Server)
49	--                0x11 (R)- Number of valid segments [31:0]:
50	--                   The value resets to 0 when new connection open is requested.
51	--                0x12 (R)- Number of dropped segments [31:0]:
52	--                   The value resets to 0 when new connection open is requested.
53	--                0x13 (R)- Counts all retransmission requests within the active connection [31:0]:
54	--                   The value resets to 0 when new connection open is requested.
55	--                0x14 (R)- Counts all reconnections from reset [31:0]:
56	--                   The value resets to 0 when module is reset.
